# Equipment affix documentation sync

## Authoritative sources

| Topic | Code (source of truth when behavior changes) | Design doc |
|-------|---------------------------------------------|------------|
| Droppable affix definitions | `AFFIX_POOL` in `frontend/src/game/equipment.js` | [docs/design/06-equipment.md](docs/design/06-equipment.md) **7.2.1** (full table: id, tier, type, display name, stat, base min/max) |
| Rare item epithets | `EPITHET_POOL` in the same file | **7.2.3** |
| Physical / spell weapon-only affixes | `PHYS_WEAPON_AFFIX_POOL`, `SPELL_WEAPON_AFFIX_POOL` in `frontend/src/game/weaponAffixPools.js` (merged in `equipment.js`) | **7.3** weapon tables |
| Other specialized affixes (orb, armor, shield, ring, etc.) | Not implemented | **7.3** (remaining subsections; mark **未实现** until wired) |

## Mandatory alignment

- **Changing `AFFIX_POOL` or `EPITHET_POOL`** (add/remove/rename entry, change `baseMin`/`baseMax`, `stat`, `type`, `tier`, or `name` / Unicode display string): update **06-equipment.md 7.2.1 and/or 7.2.3** in the **same change set**. Update **7.5** summary counts if the totals change.
- **Changing 7.2.1 or 7.2.3** in the design doc: update **`equipment.js`** pools to match in the **same change set**, unless the edit is explicitly a design-only proposal (then do not claim parity; label as future work).
- **Do not** describe live-drop affix names or numeric ranges in other sections (e.g. examples in 7.2.2) as if they were implemented unless they exist in `AFFIX_POOL`.

## Mechanic compatibility gate (mandatory)

- When designing or revising affixes (including 7.2.x/7.3 proposals), you MUST check conflicts against current game mechanics and implementation before finalizing.
- Minimum verification scope:
  - Combat formulas and timing semantics in `docs/design/03-combat.md` (turn-based only; no real-time assumptions).
  - Attribute and secondary-stat model in `docs/design/04-classes-attributes.md`.
  - Current executable fields and aggregation in `frontend/src/game/equipment.js`, `frontend/src/game/weaponAffixPools.js`, and `frontend/src/game/combat.js`.
- If an affix is design-only and not implemented yet, label it clearly as **未实现 / 候选** and do not present it as live behavior.
- If a conflict is found (missing stat field, incompatible trigger timing, unsupported stacking, contradictory formulas), resolve it in the same change set by either:
  - adjusting the affix design to fit existing mechanics, or
  - updating related docs/code/tests together to establish the new mechanic.
- Prohibited: speculative or "free-form" affix descriptions that bypass current mechanics/implementation constraints.

## Tests

- If affix generation or display logic changes, extend or adjust `frontend/src/game/equipment.spec.js` so pools and naming stay covered.

